its fixed.... 
dont know what it exaclty if one thing or many things, but its fixed and feels brand new...shifting going down the road or sitting still gears are so much closer together and the tranny feels saweeeeetttttt~!~ 

i have with ease 1-4 + reverse no troubles... 

beck and I replaced the front shift rod,front shift rod bushing,rear coupler,along with shifter and stop plate changed so thats alot new to make it all work purdy again........ 

i, it would only of had to of been the tranny or one of the bushings from the inside tube for shift rod which would have taken a engine/tranny drop i wasnt up for... everything else is replaced now..... 
 

again theres no telling what it was the good thing now is it shifts better than it ever has in our ownership .... 

thanks to all those that tried to give a suggestion on this.. 
i had no choice but to replace all that i could to make it right... 
the stop plate was a real issue here and can cause a mess out of adjustment. 

i also believe my shift rod was a little bent as well i noticed when i took my old shift coupler off...? shift coupler boots were pretty shot as well... 

there wasnt even a front bushing at all on the front shift rod and the front shift rod looked to be bent also along with the cup at the front of it was worn badly and expanded more than the other one i now have on it.. so someone has really done some ruffing on this bus or that is what got put there... 

